14/10/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- President Ion Iliescu met with visiting Albanian counterpart Alfred Moisiu on Wednesday (13 October) and reaffirmed Romania's support for Albania's NATO and EU accession bids. 
Iliescu said Bucharest would provide assistance and expertise to Albania.
Earlier this week, Azerbaijani President Ilham Aliyev visited Romania. 
According to media reports Thursday, he described the trip as a major step forward in bilateral relations. 
(Nine o'clock, Azernews - 14/10/04)
